        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "In Zend_Db_Select class, the _renderLimitoffset function tries to get the max integer that PHP can support when no count parameter is given but in 32-bits architecture, intval(9223372036854775807) returns 0 instead of reducing to the max integer.\n\n$select->from('Table')->limit(0, 5);\n\nWill give you\n\nSELECT `Table`.* FROM `Table`\n\nInstead of\n\nSELECT `Table`.* FROM `Table` LIMIT 2147483647 OFFSET 5\n\nUsing intval('9223372036854775807') - parameter as a string - will return the max value in both 32-bits and 64-bits architecture but more simply PHP_INT_MAX can be used."
        },
