            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36387",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Fixed with r19154",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-21T01:36:17.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-21T01:36:17.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36657",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=catacaustic",
                        "name": "catacaustic",
                        "displayName": "Michael Beaumont",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This goes against the documentation.   Please see http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/zend.db.select.html#zend.db.select.building.limit for expected behaviour.\r\n\r\nAccording to the documentation, the function\r\n\r\n$select->from('table')->limit(0,5);\r\n\r\nShould produce:\r\n\r\nSELECT `Table`.* FROM `Table` LIMIT 0, 5\r\n\r\nTaking the same syntax the the original reporter has for the SQL statement produced, it should be:\r\n\r\nSELECT `Table`.* FROM `Table` LIMIT 5 OFFEST 0\r\n\r\nThe current fix gives produces the opposite actions compared to what is provided in the documentation.  ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=catacaustic",
                        "name": "catacaustic",
                        "displayName": "Michael Beaumont",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-12-03T03:27:30.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-12-03T03:27:30.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36662",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=arkhamtaro",
                        "name": "arkhamtaro",
                        "displayName": "Nicolas Lenepveu",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Fisrt, the aim of the fix is to get the max integer PHP can support.\r\n\r\nSecond, the documentation is wrong according to the code :\r\n\r\n->limit(10, 20); \/\/ ->limit($row_count, $offset)\r\n\r\nwon't get \r\n\r\nLIMIT 10, 20 \/\/ [offset,] row_count\r\nor\r\nLIMIT 20 OFFSET 10\r\n\r\nbut\r\n\r\nLIMIT 20, 10\r\nor\r\nLIMIT 10 OFFSET 20\r\n\r\nThird, in the current logic of the using of limit clause, it is impossible to have a empty row count value.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=arkhamtaro",
                        "name": "arkhamtaro",
                        "displayName": "Nicolas Lenepveu",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-12-03T04:11:43.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-12-03T04:11:43.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36666",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "@Michael Beaumont: the first parameter is the count and the second is the offset\r\nIf the count equals 0, we assume that you want all values.\r\n\r\nSee http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/code\/browse\/Standard_Library\/standard\/trunk\/library\/Zend\/Db\/Select.php?r1=18750&r2=19154, for real modifications to the code or http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/code\/browse\/Standard_Library\/standard\/trunk\/tests\/Zend\/Db\/Select\/StaticTest.php?r1=19153&r2=19154 for the associated test:\r\n{code}\r\n$select->from('table1')->limit(0, 5);\r\n{code}\r\nproduces\r\n{code}\r\n'SELECT \"table1\".* FROM \"table1\" LIMIT ' . PHP_INT_MAX . ' OFFSET 5'\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-12-03T05:01:49.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-12-03T05:01:49.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37001",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "@Michael Beaumont: It appears that it's a documentation issue (see ZF-6237)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
